  <title>Motion Dimension FB Linear</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Motion Dimension<keyword>Dimension</keyword><keyword>Function-Block</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A<text style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Motion-Dimension FB</text> can define the relative position of two parts that have been joined using a Slide-Joint. One of the parts is a kinematically-defined Part, and the other Part becomes a kinematically-defined Part, a Slider, by virtue of adding the Motion-Dimension FB between the parts. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Slider">Slider</link> is a <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Motion-Driven-Part">Motion-Part</link>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small">See <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-FB-Motion-Dimension">Add Motion-Dimension FB</link></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
